1
00:00:02,025 --> 00:00:03,067
剧情回顾...

2
00:00:03,068 --> 00:00:06,023
因为瘫痪我坐了四年轮椅
I was in a wheelchair,paralyzed for four years.

3
00:00:06,024 --> 00:00:07,091
这座岛改变了我
This island, it changed me.

4
00:00:07,092 --> 00:00:09,011
让我充实
It made me whole.

5
00:00:09,012 --> 00:00:11,053
十分感谢你 John
I'm so thankful for you, John.

6
00:00:11,054 --> 00:00:13,025
你偷走了我的肾
You stole my kidney.

7
00:00:13,026 --> 00:00:15,061
你需要一个父亲而我需要一个肾
You needed a father and I needed a kidney,

8
00:00:15,062 --> 00:00:17,026
这就是现实
and that's what happened.

9
00:00:17,027 --> 00:00:18,031
忘了它吧
Get over it.

10
00:00:18,032 --> 00:00:19,084
我不在乎Jack怎么说
I don't care what Jack said.

11
00:00:19,085 --> 00:00:22,031
我们必须救他回来这是我欠他的
They've got him, and we have to get him back. I owe him that.

12
00:00:22,032 --> 00:00:23,067
你是怎么来这座岛的?
How did you get onto this island?

13
00:00:23,068 --> 00:00:25,028
他们有一艘潜艇
They brought me on the submarine.

14
00:00:25,029 --> 00:00:28,058
你们的人可以自由的来去吗?
So your people, they can just come and go whenever they want?

15
00:00:28,059 --> 00:00:32,024
你永远不会知道一颗C4也能派上用处
You never know when a little c4 might come in handy.

16
00:00:42,049 --> 00:00:44,034
姓名?
Name?

17
00:00:44,035 --> 00:00:46,035
John Locke

18
00:00:46,058 --> 00:00:48,095
婚姻状况呢 Locke先生?
Marital status, Mr. Locke?

19
00:00:49,029 --> 00:00:50,085
单身
Single.

20
00:00:50,086 --> 00:00:52,038
有女朋友吗?
Girlfriend?

21
00:00:52,039 --> 00:00:54,042
没有
No

22
00:00:56,022 --> 00:00:58,055
你的父母还活着吗?
Are your parents living?

23
00:00:59,002 --> 00:01:03,025
我是被领养的 我从来没见过自己的父母
I was raised in foster care.I never really knew my parents.

24
00:01:04,029 --> 00:01:08,031
你有没有想过 要寻找自己的亲生父母?
Have you ever considered seeking out your biological parents?

25
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:11,085
我认为这并不重要
I don't see how that's relevant.

26
00:01:11,086 --> 00:01:14,019
这很重要Locke先生 因为如果政府要
It's relevant, Mr. Locke,because if the government's

27
00:01:14,020 --> 00:01:16,082
继续支付你的残疾保险的话
gonna continue paying your disability insurance,

28
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:20,071
那我就要知道你的情况 是否有所改善
I have to figure out whether or not your condition has improved.

29
00:01:21,077 --> 00:01:25,076
那么...你的胃口怎么样?
So... How's your appetite?

30
00:01:26,083 --> 00:01:28,086
很好
Fine.

31
00:01:29,050 --> 00:01:32,068
我发现你已经 停止支付你的医疗帐单了
I see you stopped submitting your therapy bills for reimbursement.

32
00:01:32,069 --> 00:01:35,025
因为我已经不去了
It's 'cause I stopped going.

33
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:37,079
那只是浪费时间
Waste of time.

34
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:45,010
这只是临时的 Locke先生(停止残疾人保险)
It's just a temporary suspension,Mr. Locke.

35
00:01:45,011 --> 00:01:48,046
一旦你重新接受治疗 你可以再来申请
As soon as you resume your sessions,you can reapply.

36
00:01:48,047 --> 00:01:50,025
你认为我是暂时的残疾?
You think I'm temporarily disabled?

37
00:01:50,026 --> 00:01:52,071
沮丧是暂时的 所以是的
Depression can be temporary, yes.

38
00:01:52,072 --> 00:01:56,097
停止接受治疗真是明智之举
And since you see fit to stop going to therapy,I guess you're all better.

39
00:02:00,074 --> 00:02:02,074
我猜是这样的
Guess I am.

40
00:02:05,015 --> 00:02:07,017
下一个!
Next!

41
00:02:17,033 --> 00:02:19,052
这边!
Over here!

42
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:27,050
他在做什么?
What is he doing?

43
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:32,080
好身手!
Good hands!

44
00:02:39,049 --> 00:02:41,054
接的好
Nice.

45
00:02:42,067 --> 00:02:46,012
她就是那个 帮助我和Sawyer逃跑的人
She's the one who helped me and Sawyer escape.

46
00:02:46,016 --> 00:02:47,029
怎么了?
What's up?

47
00:02:47,030 --> 00:02:49,064
我想还有段时间...
I think it's gonna be a while...

48
