What do you suggest?

69
00:04:55,021 --> 00:04:58,096
等天黑的时候 当Jack一个人时我们过去...
We wait till it's dark.We approach Jack when he's alone...

70
00:05:00,032 --> 00:05:03,017
如果他想回来 我们就把他弄出来
And if he wants out, we get him out.

71
00:05:04,047 --> 00:05:05,072
这就是我们所知道的
Here's what we know, Crystal.

72
00:05:05,073 --> 00:05:10,032
昨晚两点左右 那笔玻利维亚的保险金被盗了
The bolivian coal deposits were stolen last night around 2:00 a.m.

73
00:05:10,033 --> 00:05:13,096
那就意味着"眼镜蛇"又回来了
Oh, that means the cobra...he's back.

74
00:05:15,098 --> 00:05:17,049
他被击中了吗?
Has he been shot?

75
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,050
我找不到他
I can't find him!

76
00:05:21,035 --> 00:05:24,035
他有武器 我动不了了
He's armed! I can't get up!

77
00:05:26,056 --> 00:05:29,015
你好 你是John Locke?
Hello. John Locke?

78
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:31,050
抱歉 谢绝推销
I'm sorry. No solicitors.

79
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:35,028
-有门上有标志  -我不是想要卖...
-I have a sign.  -I'm not trying to sell you...

80
00:05:35,032 --> 00:05:37,041
听着 我叫Peter Talbot
Listen, my name's Peter Talbot.

81
00:05:37,042 --> 00:05:39,044
我只想和你谈谈
I just need a couple minutes to talk to you.

82
00:05:39,045 --> 00:05:40,076
关于什么?
Talk about what?

83
00:05:40,077 --> 00:05:43,062
实际上 是我的母亲
My mother, actually.

84
00:05:43,063 --> 00:05:45,038
我认为她和你遇到了同样的麻烦
I think she might be in some trouble.

85
00:05:45,039 --> 00:05:46,093
我不是你要找的John Locke
You got the wrong John Locke.

86
00:05:46,094 --> 00:05:49,056
你有几个肾脏?
How many kidneys do you have?

87
00:05:53,066 --> 00:05:55,021
她是两个月前认识他的
She met him two months ago.

88
00:05:55,022 --> 00:05:57,066
"一见钟情" 她是这样说的
"Love at first sight," is what she said.

89
00:05:57,067 --> 00:06:01,028
那人很有魅力 很幽默
The guy was charming, sweet, funny.

90
00:06:01,033 --> 00:06:02,097
他叫Adam Seward
His name's Adam Seward.

91
00:06:02,098 --> 00:06:06,076
他是一个从安大略湖来的退休电脑承包商
He's a retired computer entrepreneur from Ontario.

92
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:12,008
Adam很特别
Anyway, Adam had something... special.

93
00:06:12,009 --> 00:06:15,002
没过多久 我母亲就为他着迷了
My mom just went gaga for him right out of the gate.

94
00:06:15,003 --> 00:06:18,027
在认识他两个月后 她答应嫁给他
After two months of knowing him,she agree to marry the guy.

95
00:06:18,028 --> 00:06:20,094
而他的一些事情...
And something about him...

96
00:06:21,013 --> 00:06:23,052
我认为他另有所图
Something in my gut told me that he was after something,

97
00:06:23,053 --> 00:06:26,037
所以我就开始调查他
so I had to check him out.

98
00:06:27,044 --> 00:06:30,003
我还是不知道 这和我有什么关系
Well, I'm not sure I know what any of this has to do with me.

99
00:06:30,004 --> 00:06:33,071
这和你的确有关系 Locke先生
Well, what this has to do with you, Mr. Locke,

100
00:06:33,075 --> 00:06:37,049
因为你捐了一个肾脏给Adam Seward
is that you donated one of your kidneys to Adam Seward,

101
00:06:37,050 --> 00:06:40,061
只是那时他的名字不同罢了
only his name was different back then.

102
00:06:40,078 --> 00:06:43,063
他曾用过"Anthony Cooper"这个名字
He used to be "Anthony Cooper."

103
00:06:48,092 --> 00:06:52,014
我能找到的只有他的医疗记录
All I could find were his medical records,

104
00:06:52,042 --> 00:06:54,016
我发现了他是一个肾脏移植的
and I saw that he was the recipient

105
00:06:54,017 --> 00:06:57,089
接受者 当然是从你那里
of a kidney transplant from You.

106
00:06:58,028 --> 00:07:01,012
我想 他骗走了别人的肾脏
So I figured, hey,someone gave the guy his kidney.

107
00:07:01,013 --> 00:07:03,024
那该有多糟啊
How bad could he be?

108
00:07:04,004 --> 00:07:06,004
是吗?
Right?

109
00:07:11,039 --> 00:07:14,079
那是一个匿名捐赠
Well, it..it was an anonymous donation.

110
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:16,080
我从来没见过他
I never met him.

111
00:07:21,057 --> 00:07:22,078
你确定吗?
Are you sure?

112
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:25,067
我很抱歉我帮不了你
Yeah, I'm sorry. I can't help you.

113
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:11,038
Sayid你守着前面
Sayid, you guard the front.

114
00:08:11,039 --> 00:08:12,091
我到后面去掩护
I'll go around and cover the back.

115
00:08:12,092 --> 00:08:14,039
你从侧门进去
You head in through the side door.

116
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,043
就我一个人进去?
I'm going in alone?

117
00:08:15,044 --> 00:08:17,099
他第一个见到你更好
It's better if you're the first one he sees.

118
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,001
好吧
All right.

119
00:09:43,047 --> 00:09:45,076
你在这里干什么?
What are you doing here?

120
00:09:45,089 --> 00:09:47,063
我是来救你的
I came to get you.

121
00:09:47,064 --> 00:09:49,035
马上离开这里
Get out of here

122
00:09:49,036 --> 00:09:50,079
快走
right now. Go.

123
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:53,013
Kate 他们在监视我!
Kate, they're watching me!

124
00:09:53,042 --> 00:09:55,010
-快离开这里!  -我不会离开你的
-Get out of here!  -I'm not leaving you.

125
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,064
-是的 你快走!  -趴下! 趴下!
-Yes, you are!  -Get down!

126
00:09:56,065 --> 00:09:58,023
别伤害她!
Don't hurt her!

127
00:09:58,024 --> 00:09:59,066
退后 医生
Step back, doc.

128
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:01,080
退后
Step back.

129
00:10:04,077 --> 00:10:06,077
看住他
Hold him still.

130
00:10:08,073 --> 00:10:10,089
和你们在一起的还有谁?
Who else is with you?

131
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:19,005
回答他的问题 Kate
Just answer the question, Kate.

132
00:10:19,061 --> 00:10:25,059
再给你一次机会,还有谁?
Okay, one more time--who else is with you?

133
00:10:29,075 --> 00:10:31,067
没人了
Nobody.

134
00:10:31,068 --> 00:10:34,025
没人了 就我们两个
Nobody else. It was just us.

135
00:11:09,026 --> 00:11:11,043
小声点
Keep your voice down.

136
00:11:11,056 --> 00:11:13,056
好吧
All right.

137
00:11:14,057 --> 00:11:15,086
没关系的 John
It's all right, John.

138
00:11:15,087 --> 00:11:17,066
你不必用枪指着我
You don't have to point the gun at me.

139
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:20,028
我会告诉你Jack在哪儿的
I can tell you where Jack is.

140
00:11:20,051 --> 00:11:22,085
我不是来找Jack的
I'm not looking for Jack.

141
00:11:25,019 --> 00:11:28,001
我是来找那潜艇的
I'm looking for the submarine.

142
00:11:31,092 --> 00:11:33,073
那艘潜艇
The submarine...

143
00:11:33,074 --> 00:11:35,009
它在哪儿?
where is it?

144
00:11:35,010 --> 00:11:37,036
我不知道你在说什么 John
I'm not sure what you mean, John.

145
00:11:37,037 --> 00:11:38,044
什么潜艇?
What submarine?

146
00:11:38,045 --> 00:11:42,019
那个可以帮你们离开这座岛的潜艇...
The one you use to travel to and from the island...

147
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:44,099
你们中的Mikhail告诉我的
The one your man Mikhail told me about

148
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,026
在他被我杀掉前
right before I killed him.

149
