00:13:50,026 --> 00:13:52,024
这看上去不错 你认为呢?
Oh, it looks good. What do you think?

186
00:13:52,025 --> 00:13:55,045
我也很喜欢 但是是不是太大了
I like it.Maybe just a little larger.

187
00:14:00,076 --> 00:14:02,093
还是大点的好
Larger would be good.

188
00:14:03,021 --> 00:14:05,068
我去那边看看
I'll go over there and take a look.

189
00:14:11,063 --> 00:14:13,035
你好 John
Hello, John.

190
00:14:13,036 --> 00:14:17,073
你最近有喜事要办?
Gonna be a big to-do or just the two of you and a preacher?

191
00:14:17,074 --> 00:14:21,019
我猜你不会邀请我的 因为当你介绍我时...
I guess you couldn't invite me, huh?That would make for...

192
00:14:21,020 --> 00:14:22,048
会很尴尬的
awkward introductions.

193
00:14:22,049 --> 00:14:23,069
你是怎么知道我...
How did you even know that I...

194
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,099
那是因为她儿子告诉我的
I know because her son came to me

195
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:29,004
还问我 我是怎么给你我的肾脏的
and asked why I gave you a kidney.

196
00:14:29,065 --> 00:14:32,010
他知道你不怀好意 只是还没有证据
He's on to you,but he doesn't have any proof.

197
00:14:32,011 --> 00:14:35,066
所以他来找我 让我作证
So he came to me hoping I would vouch for you.

198
00:14:35,081 --> 00:14:38,014
你和他说了什么?
What did you say to him?

199
00:14:39,097 --> 00:14:42,070
你在欺骗她 不是吗?
You're conning her, aren't you?

200
00:14:43,008 --> 00:14:46,052
你和她结婚是为了她的钱
You're gonna marry her for her money, right?

201
00:14:46,053 --> 00:14:48,027
你想干什么John?
What is it you want, John?

202
00:14:48,028 --> 00:14:50,045
我要你结束这一切
I want you to end it.

203
00:14:50,069 --> 00:14:53,063
我要你取消婚礼
I want you to call off the wedding.

204
00:14:54,019 --> 00:14:55,059
你为什么要这样做?
Why are you doing this?

205
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:58,053
因为这不公平
Because it's not fair.

206
00:14:58,054 --> 00:15:01,086
你让他们信任你
You make people think that you're their family,

207
00:15:01,087 --> 00:15:03,078
然后逃之夭夭 还毁了他们的生活
and then you leave their life in ruins,

208
00:15:03,079 --> 00:15:07,020
我是不会让你再这么做的
and I'm not gonna let you do it again.

209
00:15:07,065 --> 00:15:11,015
你必须取消婚礼 然后离开
You're gonna call off your engagement and go,

210
00:15:11,022 --> 00:15:13,093
否则我就告诉她真相
or I'm gonna tell her the truth.

211
00:15:15,077 --> 00:15:18,025
我想听你自己说出来
I want to hear you say it.

212
00:15:18,027 --> 00:15:20,077
你说你会离开的
You say you're gonna leave.

213
00:15:27,014 --> 00:15:29,014
好吧 John
Okay, John.

214
00:15:29,049 --> 00:15:31,049
我会的
You got it.

215
00:15:45,092 --> 00:15:49,017
能帮我拿一下轮椅吗?
Would you mind helping me get into my chair?

216
00:15:50,087 --> 00:15:53,011
我保证不耍花招
No tricks, I promise.

217
00:15:55,028 --> 00:15:57,066
我只想得到些尊严
I just want some dignity.

218
00:15:59,069 --> 00:16:04,028
你应该比任何人都明白我的意思吧
You of all people should understand what it means to want some dignity.

219
00:16:11,038 --> 00:16:13,044
谢谢你
Thank you.

220
00:16:16,087 --> 00:16:18,079
告诉我 John
So tell me, John,

221
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:20,097
你想怎么驾驶那潜艇?
how do you expect to pilot our submarine?

222
00:16:20,098 --> 00:16:23,092
那是个很复杂的机械设备
I mean, it's a complicated piece of machinery.

223
00:16:23,093 --> 00:16:25,052
不单单就是按"潜入"这么简单
You don't just press "submerge."

224
00:16:25,053 --> 00:16:28,020
我会想办法的
I'll figure something out.

225
00:16:28,043 --> 00:16:32,019
你知道 我曾是海军长官
For all you know,I was a commander in the navy.

226
00:16:35,065 --> 00:16:38,049
抓住我的脖子 我来帮你起来
Put your arm around my neck.I'll lift under your knees.

227
00:16:38,050 --> 00:16:40,089
那个包里是什么 John?
What's in the pack, John?

228
00:16:41,046 --> 00:16:43,017
如果你见到了Mikhail 那就意味着你...
If you've met Mikhail, that means

229
00:16:43,018 --> 00:16:45,068
去过那个通讯站...
you were in the communications station...

230
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:49,077
你就会找到炸药
Which means you found the explosives.

231
00:16:51,009 --> 00:16:54,071
你不是想驾驶那潜艇离开这里 对吗?
So you're not planning to pilot the submarine anywhere, are you?

232
00:16:56,073 --> 00:16:59,039
你是想炸毁它
You're planning to destroy it.

233
00:17:02,049 --> 00:17:04,077
我了解你 John Locke
I know you, John Locke.

234
00:17:08,004 --> 00:17:10,043
你什么都不知道
You don't know me at all.

235
00:17:11,023 --> 00:17:14,019
我知道你在加州出生
I know you were born in California.

236
00:17:14,055 --> 00:17:17,055
然后被领养
I know you were raised in foster care.

237
00:17:17,056 --> 00:17:20,050
你在Tustin浪费了很多时间
I know you wasted a big part of your life in Tustin

238
00:17:20,051 --> 00:17:24,066
只是在一个盒子公司里消磨自己的人生
pushing papers at a company that manufactured industrial boxes.

239
00:17:26,053 --> 00:17:27,080
我还知道 在你没来这座岛的前四年间
I know you spent the four years

240
00:17:27,081 --> 00:17:31,076
一直是靠坐轮椅的
prior to your arrival on this island in a wheelchair.

241
00:17:34,046 --> 00:17:37,027
而且我知道是什么让你坐上那轮椅的
And I know how you ended up in it.

242
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:45,040
告诉我 John...
Tell me, John...

243
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,068
你痛苦吗?
Did it hurt?

244
00:17:55,057 --> 00:17:57,094
我感到我的背被撕开了
I felt my back break.

245
00:18:00,015 --> 00:18:02,020
你认为呢?
What do you think?

246
00:18:27,021 --> 00:18:30,082
没想到那么快又见面了 Kate
I didn't think I'd see you again so soon, Kate.

247
00:18:34,031 --> 00:18:36,052
小心点
Be careful in here.

248
00:18:37,017 --> 00:18:39,017
谢谢
Thanks.

249
00:18:57,036 --> 00:18:59,042
他们伤害你了吗?
Did they hurt you?

250
00:19:00,059 --> 00:19:02,013
没有
No

251
00:19:02,014 --> 00:19:04,014
你呢?
Did they hurt you?

252
00:19:05,090 --> 00:19:07,090
没有
No

253
00:19:11,060 --> 00:19:13,060
这些都是什么?
What is all this?

254
00:19:14,091 --> 00:19:17,024
这就是他们住的地方
This is where they live.

255
00:19:18,091 --> 00:19:21,030
那他们抓的人呢?
And the people they took?

256
00:19:21,077 --> 00:19:23,007
孩子们呢?
The kids?

257
00:19:23,008 --> 00:19:25,008
他们都很安全
They're all safe.

258
00:19:27,073 --> 00:19:29,073
"安全"?
"Safe"?

259
00:19:34,084 --> 00:19:37,003
你和他们现在是一伙的吗?
So you're with them now?

260
00:19:39,032 --> 00:19:42,000
我不属于任何一方 Kate
I'm not with anyone, Kate.

261
00:19:45,045 --> 00:19:47,079
他们对你做了什么?
What did they do to you?

262
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,039
-什么都没有  -那你为什么要这样?
-Nothing.  -Then why are you acting like this?

263
00:19:51,051 --> 00:19:53,055
没有办法...
There's no way...

264
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:55,009
你...我没办法...
You... There's no way that I could...

265
00:19:55,010 --> 00:19:56,026
我是来帮你的
I came here to help you!

266
00:19:56,027 --> 00:19:57,036
你为什么不告诉我...
So why don't you tell me...

267
00:19:57,037 --> 00:20:00,059
我告诉你不要回来找我
I told you not to come back here for me.

268
00:20:01,007 --> 00:20:03,063
我不认为你是真心的
I didn't think you meant it.

269
00:20:40,073 --> 00:20:43,040
他们对你做了什么 Jack?
What did they do to you, Jack?

270
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:51,053
我和他们做了笔交易
I made a deal with them.

271
00:20:52,031 --> 00:20:54,065
他们会放我走的
They're gonna let me go.

272
00:20:57,056 --> 00:20:59,056
去哪儿?
Where?

273
00:21:01,042 --> 00:21:03,045
回家
Home.

274
00:21:10,084 --> 00:21:12,063
什么时候?
When?

275
00:21:12,064 --> 00:21:15,014
早晨的第一件事
First thing in the morning.

276
00:21:17,046 --> 00:21:19,055
我会去找救援的 这是唯一的机会
I can bring back help.It's our best chance.

277
00:21:19,056 --> 00:21:20,081
你相信这些人?
You trust these people?

278
00:21:20,082 --> 00:21:22,040
他们是骗子 你为什么会相信...
They are liars. Why would you believe...

279
00:21:22,041 --> 00:21:25,085
当你求我救Swayer的时候
I trust them because you told me to, Kate...

280
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:30,055
是你让我相信他们的 Kate
When you asked me to save Sawyer's life.

281
00:21:39,019 --> 00:21:41,047
他们和你说了什么?
What did they tell you?

282
00:21:46,024 --> 00:21:49,025
Jack 我们要走了
Jack, we need to go.

283
00:21:51,072 --> 00:21:53,083
我一会儿就去
I'll be right there.

284
00:22:02,034 --> 00:22:06,010
我让你不要回来找我 我也希望...
I asked you not to come back here for me, and I wish...

285
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,027
希望你不会来
I wish that you hadn't.

286
00:22:16,096 --> 00:22:19,069
但我一定会回来找你的
But I will come back here for you.

287
00:22:53,014 --> 00:22:55,025
John Locke?

288
00:22:55,043 --> 00:22:56,087
Mason探长
Detective Mason.

289
00:22:56,088 --> 00:22:59,051
这位是Reed探长 介意我们问你几个问题吗?
That's detective Reed. Do you mind if we ask you a few questions?

290
00:22:59,052 --> 00:23:00,054
当然不
No, of course not.

291
00:23:00,055 --> 00:23:03,048
你认识一个叫Peter Talbot的人吗?
Do you know a man named Peter Talbot?

292
00:23:06,025 --> 00:23:07,048
不 我不认识
No, I don't think so.

293
00:23:07,049 --> 00:23:10,040
偏瘦 棕色头发 大约20岁
Thin, brown hair, 20.

294
00:23:10,041 --> 00:23:14,078
我们知道两天前他来过你的公寓
If it'll be helpful,we believe he was here in your apartment two days ago.

295
00:23:15,072 --> 00:23:17,020
是的 他是个推销员
Yeah, he was a solicitor.

296
00:23:17,021 --> 00:23:19,005
我把他轰走了
I sent him away.

297
00:23:19,006 --> 00:23:23,074
Talbot先生家的资产有大约200万
Mr.Talbot's family is worth somewhere in the neighborhood of $200 million.

298
00:23:23,075 --> 00:23:26,076
我很好奇 他怎么会去做推销员呢?
So I'm curious. What exactly was he selling you door-to-door?

299
00:23:26,077 --> 00:23:28,096
我告诉过你了 我不认识他
Well, I...Look, I told you I don't know him.

300
00:23:28,097 --> 00:23:33,014
那为什么他口袋里的纸上写着你的地址呢?
Then why was your name and address on a piece of paper in his pocket?

301
00:23:35,019 --> 00:23:38,038
你们为什么会找他的口袋?
Why were you... would you be looking through his pockets?

302
00:23:38,039 --> 00:23:40,095
因为Peter Talbot's已经死了
Because Peter Talbot's dead.

303
00:23:46,075 --> 00:23:49,025
这不容易...
It wasn't easy, you know...

304
00:23:50,016 --> 00:23:52,075
整天和你在你的舱里...
Being in that hatch with you all that time...

305
00:23:52,076 --> 00:23:55,065
你总是走来走去
Knowing you had no business walking around,

306
00:23:55,066 --> 00:23:59,062
如果我不告诉你我的真实身份 就连问你的资格都没有
knowing I couldn't even ask you about it without telling you who I really was.

307
00:23:59,063 --> 00:24:01,063
现在你可以问我了...
So ask me now...

308
00:24:03,039 --> 00:24:06,048
我已经知道你的真实身份了
Now that I know who you really are.

309
00:24:10,010 --> 00:24:11,064
那很快吗?
Was it immediate?

310
00:24:11,065 --> 00:24:14,059
你一来这个地方就开始了吗?
It started the moment you got here?

311
00:24:15,098 --> 00:24:17,095
你就这样能走路了 就像人生的回归
And you were just walking,the feeling returned

312
00:24:17,096 --> 00:24:19,045
就是坠机那天 对吗?
right after the crash, that day?

313
00:24:19,046 --> 00:24:22,025
那就是"快"的意思 Ben
That's what "immediate" means, Ben.

314
00:24:24,012 --> 00:24:27,055
你在想为什么你还不能恢复
You're wondering why it hasn't happened for you.

315
00:24:27,076 --> 00:24:31,007
你的伤只能慢慢恢复
You're not recovering as fast as you like.

316
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:34,097
Jack帮你手术到现在多久了?
How long's it been since Jack fixed you?

317
00:24:34,098 --> 00:24:36,092
一个星期?
A week?

318
00:24:36,093 --> 00:24:38,098
我仔细一想
Now that I think about it,

319
00:24:38,099 --> 00:24:40,076
原来你是怎么得病的?
how did you get sick in the first place?

320
00:24:40,077 --> 00:24:43,065
你害怕那会消失吗 John?
Are you afraid it'll go away, John?

321
00:24:43,089 --> 00:24:45,081
这就是你想炸毁那潜艇的原因吧!
Is that why you want to destroy the submarine?

322
00:24:45,082 --> 00:24:47,055
因为你知道如果你离开这座岛
'Cause you know if you leave the island,

323
00:24:47,056 --> 00:24:49,081
你又得回到轮椅上了
you'll be back in the chair?

324
00:24:53,012 --> 00:24:55,046
你有吃的东西吗?
You got anything to eat?

325
00:25:16,023 --> 00:25:19,052
回家去吧 孩子 你知道你不该在这儿的
Go on home,kid.You know you're not supposed to be here.

326
00:25:19,053 --> 00:25:22,042
我父亲要我来拿他的包
My father sent me to get his pack.

327
00:25:25,008 --> 00:25:26,053
为什么?
Why?

328
00:25:26,054 --> 00:25:29,070
我不知道Ryan 但是他叫我来拿的
I don't know,Ryan,but he told me to get it.

329
00:25:29,071 --> 00:25:31,071
好吧
All right.

330
00:25:32,002 --> 00:25:34,002
拿去吧
Here you go.

331
00:25:38,073 --> 00:25:41,006
你是Alex 对吗?
You're Alex, aren't you?

332
00:25:43,054 --> 00:25:45,087
你是怎么知道我名字的?
How do you know my name?

333
00:25:46,011 --> 00:25:48,088
因为你和你母亲长的很像
Because you look like your mother.

334
00:25:51,002 --> 00:25:53,011
我母亲已经死了
My mother is dead.

335
00:25:54,035 --> 00:25:57,020
我相信他们是这么和你说的
I'm sure that's what they told you.

336
00:25:59,006 --> 00:26:01,006
快走吧 Alex!
Get going, Alex!

337
00:26:08,016 --> 00:26:10,039
你给我闭嘴
Keep your mouth shut.

338
00:26:18,004 --> 00:26:19,093
你们的电是从哪里来的?
Where do you get electricity?

339
00:26:19,094 --> 00:26:22,018
我们有两个巨大的"仓鼠"来转动那个发电盘
We have two giant hamsters running on a massive wheel

340
00:26:22,019 --> 00:26:25,049
-我们地下有个秘密的兽穴  -这真有趣
-at our secret underground lair.  -Yeah, that's funny.

341
00:26:25,085 --> 00:26:29,020
冰箱里还有一些剩菜 你自便吧
There's leftovers in the refrigerator.Help yourself.

342
00:26:39,052 --> 00:26:42,062
很抱歉我喜欢吃禽类
I ate most of the dark meat. Sorry.

343
00:26:46,068 --> 00:26:51,057
我好久没品尝鸡的味道了
I never really appreciated chicken until right now.

344
00:26:52,089 --> 00:26:55,013
我知道你要这么做 John
I know you think you need to do this, John,

345
00:26:55,014 --> 00:26:56,093
但如果你炸了我的潜艇
but if you blow up my submarine,

346
00:26:56,094 --> 00:26:59,039
我就要遇到很大的麻烦了
I'll have a big problem with my people.

347
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:02,088
你这是在奉劝我不要这么做吗?
Is that supposed to be an incentive not to blow it up?

348
00:27:05,006 --> 00:27:07,015
我出生在这个岛上
I was born on this island.

349
00:27:07,016 --> 00:27:09,010
没有几个人和我是一样的
Not many of my people can say that.

350
00:27:09,011 --> 00:27:11,026
大多数人都是因招募而被带到这里来的
Most of them were recruited and brought here.

351
00:27:11,027 --> 00:27:13,036
他们越爱这座岛
And as much as they love this place,

352
00:27:13,037 --> 00:27:15,059
就越会不惜一切代价来保护这座岛
as much as they would do anything to defend it,

353
00:27:15,060 --> 00:27:19,011
他们需要知道他们能离开这里
they need to know they can leave if they want to.

354
00:27:19,063 --> 00:27:22,082
而那艘潜艇维系着他们的希望
The sub maintains that illusion.

355
00:27:22,083 --> 00:27:23,092
那你是在欺骗他们
So you're lying to 'em.

356
00:27:23,093 --> 00:27:26,038
不 他们是自愿留下的
No. They're here because they want to be here.

357
00:27:26,039 --> 00:27:30,055
有些人只是还没有完全接受
Some of them are just not ready to make a full... commitment yet.

358
00:27:31,019 --> 00:27:33,019
但你 John...
But you, John...

359
00:27:34,065 --> 00:27:36,079
你已经做出了选择
You've already made that commitment,

360
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:38,019
而现在你有一个选择
and now you have a choice.

361
00:27:38,020 --> 00:27:40,035
停下好好想想
Because if you stop and if you think,

362
00:27:40,036 --> 00:27:42,081
我能给你看样东西
I can show you things...

363
00:27:42,082 --> 00:27:46,033
那样你想了很久的东西
things I know you want to see very badly.

364
00:27:47,087 --> 00:27:50,081
让我说的明白一点
Let me put it so you'll understand.

365
00:27:53,031 --> 00:27:55,036
想象一下这里有个盒子
Picture a box.

366
00:27:56,008 --> 00:27:59,003
你很了解盒子的 是吗 John?
You know something about boxes,don't you, John?

367
00:27:59,004 --> 00:28:01,068
如果我告诉你在这座岛的某处
What if I told you that somewhere on this island

